# Branch, PR, and publish workflow

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), [docs/contributing.md](../../docs/contributing.md), and [docs/publishing.md](../../docs/publishing.md) before changing this repo.

## Git

- Branch from `main` with `feature/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, or `chore/` prefix.
- No direct commits to `main` unless the user explicitly asks.
- Never push to `main` without explicit user approval.
- Commits only when the user asks; use Conventional Commits.

## Pre-PR

- Run `npm run validate`.
- Update `CHANGELOG.md` (`## [Unreleased]`) and `docs/CURRENT_PRODUCT_SURFACE.md` when the surface changes.
- Never stage secrets or `.env` files.
- Branch prefixes (`feature/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, `chore/`) are enforced in CI on PRs.

## Pull requests

- `gh pr create` only when the user asks.
- Do not merge, approve, or push without explicit approval. Prefer squash merge.

## Publishing

- **Never** run the publish workflow or `npm publish` unless the user explicitly requests it.
- npm, git tag `vX.Y.Z`, and GitHub Release `vX.Y.Z` must stay in sync (see publishing.md).
